<id>http://forums.nesdev.com/viewtopic.php?t=5146&amp;p=46624#p46624</id>
<link href="http://forums.nesdev.com/viewtopic.php?t=5146&amp;p=46624#p46624"/>
<title type="html"><![CDATA[Implement Wii remote support in NES emulator?]]></title>

<content type="html" xml:base="http://forums.nesdev.com/viewtopic.php?t=5146&amp;p=46624#p46624"><![CDATA[
Gotta bring up Lua scripting again. You could code a Lua-compatible C-module providing an interface to one of the wiimote libraries available for your os (e.g. wiiuse).<br /><br />I've tried this in Snes9x to play F-Zero with the Wii Wheel. That's probably nothing Glovepie couldn't do, but if you need more control over the game  Lua allows to enhance and alter some of its inner workings without having to mess with the emulator's source. Well, to a certain extent at least... The current Lua implementation still has its weaknesses.<br /><br />As far as I know Lua scripting is supported by four emulators already: FCEUX, Snes9x, Gens and VBA.<p>Statistics: Posted by <a href="http://forums.nesdev.com/memberlist.php?mode=viewprofile&amp;u=1377">miau</a> — Thu May 07, 2009 7:45 am</p><hr />
]]></content>
