<entry>
<author><name><![CDATA[Kasumi]]></name></author>
<updated>2009-05-06T23:30:19-07:00</updated>
<published>2009-05-06T23:30:19-07:00</published>
<id>http://forums.nesdev.com/viewtopic.php?t=5146&amp;p=46609#p46609</id>
<link href="http://forums.nesdev.com/viewtopic.php?t=5146&amp;p=46609#p46609"/>
<title type="html"><![CDATA[Implement Wii remote support in NES emulator?]]></title>

<content type="html" xml:base="http://forums.nesdev.com/viewtopic.php?t=5146&amp;p=46609#p46609"><![CDATA[
To my knowledge, no emulator for PC supports something like this natively, but there isn't too much need. There are already <a href="http://www.wiili.org/index.php/GlovePIE:Punch-out" class="postlink">scripts</a> for  <a href="http://carl.kenner.googlepages.com/glovepie_download" class="postlink">glovepie</a> that can accomplish such things, and if you don't like the ones available, you can write your own. (Your PC needs bluetooth)<br /><br />As well if you have a homebrew enabled Wii, this kind of thing might be supported by its NES emulator sometime soon. The author of the <a href="http://wiibrew.org/wiki/FCE_Ultra_GX" class="postlink">Wii NES emulator</a> (Tantric) has already added such a feature to <a href="http://wiibrew.org/wiki/Visual_Boy_Advance_GX" class="postlink">his GBA emulator.</a> I've tried his Kirby's Tilt And Tumble Wiimote controls, and I've gotta tell you, they rock. (Though they don't seem to return the full range of value the original game did. The main game is playable, but not some of the minigames)<br /><br />He also did custom Wii controls for some other game boy/color/advance games like Link's Awakening with Twilight Princess controls, though I admit I haven't tried them. He might add such things to his NES emulator too. That of course, only matters if you have a homebrew Wii. <br /><br />In short: Get Glovepie.<br /><br />Also I agree with Dwedit who posted while I was writing this. Punchout is kind of intolerant to lag, and you do get laggy input from a Wiimote on a PC.<p>Statistics: Posted by <a href="http://forums.nesdev.com/memberlist.php?mode=viewprofile&amp;u=3504">Kasumi</a> — Wed May 06, 2009 11:30 pm</p><hr />
]]></content>
