<title type="html"><![CDATA[Implement Wii remote support in NES emulator?]]></title>

<content type="html" xml:base="http://forums.nesdev.com/viewtopic.php?t=5146&amp;p=46606#p46606"><![CDATA[
Tonight I had a weird but interesting dream I thought I should share.. <img src="http://forums.nesdev.com/images/smilies/icon_smile.gif" alt=":)" title="Smile" /><br /><br />In my dream I played a NES emulator on my PC using a wii-remote. But the thing was, the games were adjusted for wii-remote usage. <br />Imagine "Punch Out" for example. A hit-like motion with the remote, triggered a normal high-punch (as you do it with the NES controller), and dodging left or right was accomplished with side-step motions.<br /><br />When I woke up I thought about this and I think it sounded quite cool. Would it be possible to implement this kind of control in emulators? I know people have managed to connect their wii remotes to their PC so...<br /><br />Perhaps a standard set of motions could be defined and with each game you could define that, for example &lt;up+a&gt; on NES controller also is defined by moving the wii remote up?<br /><br />Hope you understand what I mean.<p>Statistics: Posted by <a href="http://forums.nesdev.com/memberlist.php?mode=viewprofile&amp;u=353">oRBIT2002</a> — Wed May 06, 2009 10:58 pm</p><hr />
